CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 22, 1945, pg. 14, reads: "Embryo Artists - Pupils from Weil school and Vann school attended an exhibition of the paintings of John W. Gore at the Centre Avenue branch YMCA last Thursday.  The artist gave a short talk.  The art exhibit is under the auspices of the newly formed Art Society of the Centre Avenue branch. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Audience of school children in Centre Avenue YMCA for exhibition and lecture by artist John W. Gore
